{{Infobox language |name=Alur |nativename=Lur |region=[[Orientale Province]] ([[Democratic Republic of Congo]]) and [[Uganda]] |ethnicity=[[Alur people|Alur]] |speakers={{sigfig|1.37|2}} million |date=2001–2002 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam2=[[Eastern Sudanic languages|Eastern Sudanic]] |fam3=[[Nilotic languages|Nilotic]] |fam4=[[Western Nilotic languages|Western]] |fam5=[[Luo languages|Luo]] |fam6=[[Southern Luo]] |fam7=Luo–Acholi |fam8=Alur–Acholi |iso3=alz |glotto=alur1250 |glottorefname=Alur }}
'''Alur''' (Dho-Alur [d̟ɔ.a.lur]) is a [[Western Nilotic]] language spoken in the southern [[West Nile region]] of [[Uganda]] and the northeastern [[Ituri Province]] of the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]]. The language's subialects are Jokot, Jonam/Lo-Naam (mainly spoken in the Democratic Republic of the Congo), Mambisa and Wanyoro.
== Phonology ==
'''Vowels'''
Alur has 9 vowels.
