=== Nasal assimilation === Chiquitano has regressive assimilation triggered by nasal nuclei {{IPA|/ ɨ̃ ĩ ũ õ ã ẽ/}} and targeting [[consonant]] [[Syllable onset|onset]]s within a morpheme. * {{IPA|/suβũ/}} → {{IPA|[suˈmũ]}} 'parrot (sp.)' <ref>{{cite journal |last1=Sans|first1=Pierric |last2= |first2= |year=2011 |title=Proceedings of the VII Encontro Macro-Jê.Brasilia, Brazil |journal=|volume=|issue= |pages= |publisher= |doi= |url= |accessdate= }}</ref>
== Syllable structure == The language has CV, CVV, and CVC syllables. It does not allow complex onsets or codas. The only codas allowed are nasal consonants.
