'''Komi Dje''' (Ԃ&nbsp;ԃ; italics: <span style="font-family: times, Times New Roman, serif; font-size: larger">''Ԃ&nbsp;ԃ''</span>) is a letter of the [[Molodtsov alphabet]], a variant of [[Cyrillic script|Cyrillic]]. It was used only in the writing of the [[Komi language]] in the 1920s and in the [[Mordvin language]].{{citation needed | date=April 2011 | reason=not shown anywhere in the Mordvin language articles}}

Komi Dje represents the [[voiced palatal stop]] {{IPA|/ɟ/}}.

