The '''Seimat language''' is one of three [[Western Admiralty Islands languages]], the other two being [[Wuvulu-Aua language|Wuvulu-Aua]] and the extinct [[Kaniet language|Kaniet]]. The language is spoken by approximately 1000 people on the [[Ninigo Islands|Ninigo]] and the [[Anchorite Islands]] in western [[Manus Province]] of [[Papua New Guinea]].<ref name=Ethnologue>[http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=ssg Ethnologue report for Seimat]</ref> It has [[subject–verb–object|SVO word order]].<ref name=Ethnologue/>
