'''Tadaksahak''' (also ''Daoussahak, Dausahaq'' and other spellings, after the Tuareg name for its speakers, '''''Dăwsăhak''''')<ref>{{cite book|last1=Ritter|first1=Georg|title=Wörterbuch zur Sprache und Kultur der Twareg II Deutsch-Twareg|date=2009|publisher=Harrassowitz|location=Wiesbaden|page=735}}</ref> is a [[Songhay language]] spoken by the [[Pastoralism|pastoralist]] [[Idaksahak]] of the [[Ménaka Region]] of [[Mali]]. Its phonology, verb morphology and vocabulary has been strongly influenced by the neighbouring [[Tuareg languages]] [[Tamasheq]] and [[Tamajaq (disambiguation)|Tamajaq]].

